## Interview Process

Ask the developer these streamlined questions:

### 1. Project Name (Required)
```
What would you like to name this quick project?
(Use kebab-case, e.g., 'fix-auth-timeout' or 'add-workflow-labels')
Note: This will be automatically prefixed with today's date (YYYYMMDD), a sequence number (NN), 
and placed in the current month folder (YYYY-MM)
```

### 2. Brief Description (Required)
```
Briefly describe what this project does (1-2 sentences):
```

### 3. Primary Goal (Required)
```
What is the main goal or desired outcome?
(e.g., "Fix authentication timeout causing login failures")
```

### 4. Technology Stack (Required)
```
What technology stack are you using?
(e.g., "Go/Bazel", "TypeScript/React", "Java/gRPC", "Proto/Buf", "Dart/Flutter")
```

### 5. Affected Components (Required)
```
Which components or areas will be changed?
(e.g., "workflow-runner service", "auth APIs", "CLI commands", "mobile app UI")
```

### 6. Initial Task Breakdown (Optional)
```
Do you already have an idea of the tasks, or should I suggest a breakdown?
(If they provide tasks, use them. Otherwise, propose a 2-4 task breakdown based on the goal)
```

### 7. Success Criteria (Optional)
```
How will you know this is complete? (Optional - I can infer from the goal)
```

